[[File:Whitney State Forest Virginia border sign.jpg|thumb|250px|Property border sign at [[Whitney State Forest]] in [[Fauquier County, Virginia]]]]<!--The uploader of this file encourages its replacement with a better image-->
The '''[[Virginia]] state forest system''' includes 24 state-managed forests covering a total of {{convert|68626|acre|sqmi_km2|1}}.<ref name=VDOF_list>{{cite web |url=http://www.dof.virginia.gov/stateforest/acreage-totals.htm |title=Acreage |publisher=Virginia Department of Forestry |accessdate=December 29, 2016}}</ref> They are managed by the [[Virginia Department of Forestry]].
The system was created to manage and maintain forests for wildlife, [[timber]] production, recreation, water quality, and [[aesthetics]]. The system receives no taxpayer funds, and is self-supported by the sale of forest products.<ref name=SF_descript>{{cite web |url=http://www.dof.virginia.gov/stateforest/index.htm |title=Virginia's Forests, Our State Forests |publisher=Virginia Department of Forestry |accessdate=December 29, 2016}}</ref>
Most Virginia state forests are accessible to the public. Activities such as hiking, biking, horseback riding, hunting, and fishing are permitted in some state forests; permissible uses vary between individual state forests. Some activities require the purchase of a "State Forest Use Permit" for individuals ages 16 or older.<ref name=VDOF_rec>{{cite web |url=http://www.dof.virginia.gov/stateforest/recreation/index.htm |title=Recreation |publisher=Virginia Department of Forestry |accessdate=December 29, 2016}}</ref><ref name=VDOF_forests>{{cite web |url=http://www.dof.virginia.gov/print/stateforest/VAs-State-Forests.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321192616/http://www.dof.virginia.gov/print/stateforest/VAs-State-Forests.pdf |archivedate=March 21, 2015 |title=Virginia's State Forests |publisher=Virginia Department of Forestry |accessdate=December 29, 2016}}</ref>
