r Sanctuary]] || [[Franklin Lakes, New Jersey|Franklin Lakes]] || Bergen || Gateway Region || 14 acres, operated by the New Jersey Audubon Society |- | [[Manasquan Reservoir|Manasquan Reservoir Environmental Center]] || [[Howell Township, New Jersey|Howell]] || Monmouth || Shore Region || 1,204 acre park, 5 mile perimeter trail around the reservoir, center focus is wetlands ecology and wildlife and habitat protection |- | [[Meadowlands Environment Center]] || [[Lyndhurst, New Jersey|Lyndhurst]] || Bergen || Gateway Region || Operated by Ramapo College of New Jersey, wetlands trails and education programs |- | [[Merrill Creek Reservoir]] || [[Harmony Township, New Jersey|Harmony Township]] || [[Warren County, New Jersey|Warren]] || Skylands Region || 650-acre artificial lake surrounded by 290 acres of protected woodland and fields, visitor center exhibits, environmental education programs |- | [[New Jersey Audubon Society|Nature Center of Cape May]] || [[Cape May, New Jersey|Cape May]] || Cape May ||South Jersey || Operated by the New Jersey Audubon Society, features a gallery with exhibits from local artists, aquariums, a second story viewing deck and a third story viewing tower |- |New Weis Center for Education, Arts & Recreation || [[Ringwood, New Jersey|Ringwood]] ||Passaic ||Gateway Region || [http://www.highlandsnaturefriends.org website], 152-acre environmental, nature and education center; located in the former Weis Ecology Center |- | Palmyra Cove Nature Park || [[Palmyra, New Jersey|Palmyra]] || [[Burlington County, New Jersey|Burlington]] || Delaware River Region || [http://www.palmyracove.org/ website], 250 acres on the Delaware River just south of the [[Tacony Palmyra Bridge]] |- | Paws Farm Nature Center || [[Mount Laurel, New Jersey|Mount Laurel]] || Burlington || Delaware River Region || [http://www.pawsfarm.com/ website], owned by the Town, 9 acres, farm and other animals, children's themed play areas, trails |- | [[New Jersey Audubon Society|Plainsb